column12: Measurement condition : Debris; Mostly Cloudy , Light Rain , Calm Wind Swirling/Variable
column13: Beaver dam roughly 150 meters downstream, new dam being built roughly 100 meters downstream.
column14: No flow at gauge, beaver dam downstream has audible trickle through branches but cannot find the water to estimate. No flow above or below dam. Below dam restricted, assumed by another dam downstream. Based on small trickle sound and no observed flow assumed 0.001m3/s. Flattened vegetation at gauge pool suggests a large increase in stage and discharge earlier in year, which aligns with a large spike in late July. Station found with dead battery, installed new battery and then reset to found water level. Stage stable, no flow or variation. Logged stage still reading accurate water level. Logger stopped recording at 4:00, gap in record for 5 hours, 0.010m increase during this gap. Vegetation at gauge flattened, appears to be due to large flow through culvert. Large spike in stage in late July likely valid based on vegetation. Other Methods Estimated
